$11) 6. d4 $14 d5 7. exd6 Qxd6 8. Ng5 (8. h3 Nf6 $11) 8... h5 (8... Nf6 $142 $5
$15 {is worth looking at}) 9. Ne4 $14 {White threatens to win material: Ne4xd6.
White forks: c5+d6} Qd8 10. Be3 $4 {gives the opponent new chances} (10. h3
$142 Nf6 11. Nxc5 $16) 10... cxd4 $17 11. cxd4 Bb4+ (11... f5 12. Nec3 $17) 12.
Nbc3 $15 Nxe3 {Black forks: c4, g2+d1} (12... f5 13. Bg5 Qxd4 14. Qxd4 Nxd4 15.
Rd1 fxe4 16. Rxd4 $15) 13. fxe3 $11 {Black has the pair of bishops} Qh4+ 14.
Nf2 e5 {Black threatens to win material: e5xd4} 15. Qf3 {White threatens to
win material: Qf3xf7} Qe7 (15... O-O $142 {and Black could well hope to play on
} 16. g3 Qg5 $15) 16. O-O $16 O-O $2 (16... Bxc3 $142 $5 17. bxc3 f5 $16) 17.
Qxh5 $18 exd4 (17... Bxc3 18. bxc3 exd4 19. exd4 Nd8 $18) 18. Nd5 (18. Nfe4
$142 {a pity that White didn't try this} Be6 19. Ng5 Qxg5 20. Qxg5 Bxc4 21. Ne4
$18) 18... Qe5 $16 19. Qf3 (19. Qh4 dxe3 20. Ne4 $18) 19... dxe3 $4 {Black has
let it slip away.} (19... Bd6 20. g3 Be6 $11) 20. Nd3 $18 Qd4 (20... Qe6 $142
21. Qh5 Be7 $18) 21. Qxe3 $4 {what a pity, victory was in sight.} (21. N3xb4
$142 {White has the better game} e2+ 22. Rf2 $18) 21... Qxe3+ 22. Nxe3 Bd2 {
Black threatens to win material: Bd2xe3} 23. Nd5 Nd4 (23... Be6 $5 {is an
interesting idea} 24. Rad1 Rfd8 25. Rxd2 Bxd5 $11) 24. Rad1 {White threatens
to win material: Rd1xd2} (24. Ne5 b5 25. Rad1 $16) 24... Bh6 $2 (24... Bg5 25.
Nc7 Rb8 26. Rxf7 Rxf7 27. Ne5 $14) 25. Ne7+ (25. Ne5 $142 b5 26. Nxf7 bxc4 27.
Nxh6+ gxh6 28. Rxf8+ Kxf8 29. Rxd4 $18) 25... Kh8 $4 {another bit of territory
lost} (25... Kh7 $142 $5 26. Nxc8 Be3+ 27. Kh1 Raxc8 28. Bxf7 Nc6 $16) 26. Ne5
(26. Ng6+ {makes it even easier for White} Kg8 27. Nxf8 Be3+ 28. Kh1 Bf5 $18)
26... Ne6 $4 {the pressure is too much, Black crumbles} (26... Be6 $142 27.
Bxe6 Nxe6 28. Nxf7+ Kh7 29. Nxh6 gxh6 $18) 27. N5g6+ fxg6 28. Nxg6+ Kh7 29.
Nxf8+ Nxf8 30. Rxf8 g6 (30... Be3+ {cannot undo what has already been done} 31.
Kh1 Bc5 32. Bd3+ g6 33. Rf7+ Kh6 34. Rc1 $18) 31. Rf7+ (31. Bg8+ {might be the
shorter path} Kg7 32. Rdd8 Be3+ 33. Kf1 Bc5 $18) 31... Bg7 32. Rd4 Bf5 (32...
Kh6 {the last chance for counterplay} 33. Rd8 Be6 34. Rxa8 Bxc4 35. Rxb7 Bd4+
36. Kh1 Bxa2 $18) 33. Rh4+ Kg8 34. Rxf5# 1-0

