{B51: Sicilian: Moscow Variation (3 Bb5+) without 3...Bd7} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6
3. Bb5+ Nc6 4. O-O Nf6 5. e5 Nd5 (5... Nd7 6. exd6 e6 7. d4 Bxd6 8. d5 exd5 9.
Qxd5 Be7 10. Bf4 Nb4 11. Qb3 a6 12. Ne5 O-O 13. Bxd7 Bxd7 14. Rd1 Be6 15. Rxd8
Rfxd8 16. c4 f6 17. Nf3 Rd3 18. Nc3 b5 19. Nd2 Rad8 20. Re1 {Andreikin,D (2625)
-Dovzik,J (2366) Alushta 2009 1-0}) (5... dxe5 6. Nxe5 Bd7 7. Nxc6 Bxc6 8.
Bxc6+ bxc6 9. d3 e6 10. Qe2 Bd6 11. Nc3 O-O 12. Ne4 Be7 13. Nxf6+ Bxf6 14. Rb1
Qa5 15. a3 Rab8 16. b3 Bc3 17. a4 e5 18. Qe4 Qc7 19. Qc4 Qa5 20. Rd1 {Lewtak,D
(2265)-Cukrowski,F (2186) Olsztyn 2013 1-0 (93)}) 6. c4 $146 {White threatens
to win material: c4xd5} (6. d4 Qb6 (6... Nc7 7. Bxc6+ bxc6 8. dxc5 Ba6 9. Re1
dxc5 10. Nbd2 Qd5 11. b3 c4 12. bxc4 Bxc4 13. Re4 Ba6 14. c4 Qd7 15. Ba3 Ne6
16. Qa4 Bb7 17. Nb3 c5 18. Qxd7+ Kxd7 19. Rd1+ Ke8 20. Re3 Ba6 21. Bxc5 {
Koziak,V (2489)-Tazbir,M (2444) Karpacz 2008 1/2-1/2 (39)}) 7. c4 Nc7 8. exd6
Nxb5 9. dxc5 Qxc5 10. cxb5 Qxb5 11. Nc3 Qa5 12. Nd5 exd6 13. Re1+ Be6 14. Ng5
Kd7 15. Nf4 Nd8 16. Nfxe6 fxe6 17. Bd2 Qd5 18. Qe2 Rc8 19. Rad1 Rc2 20. Qe3 Qc5
{De Jong,T (2345)-Pliester,L (2400) Wijk aan Zee 1991 1-0 (38)}) (6. Bxc6+ bxc6
7. b3 Bg4 8. Bb2 dxe5 9. Bxe5 f6 10. Bb2 e5 11. d3 Be7 12. Nbd2 O-O 13. a4 g5
14. a5 Rb8 15. Ra4 Rb4 16. Qa1 Qd7 17. c3 Rxa4 18. Qxa4 Nf4 19. d4 e4 20. Nxe4
Bxf3 {Schweiger,G (2245)-Stoll,T (2215) Porto San Giorgio 1996 0-1}) (6. Re1 e6
$14) 6... Nc7 $14 7. Bxc6+ bxc6 8. d3 e6 (8... g6 9. exd6 Qxd6 10. Nc3 $14) 9.
Bg5 Be7 10. exd6 {White forks: c7+e7} Qxd6 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 {White has a new
backward pawn: d3} 12. Ne5 {White threatens to win material: Ne5xc6} Bb7 13. f4
O-O 14. Nc3 Rad8 15. Qc2 f6 {Black threatens to win material: f6xe5} 16. Nf3
Qd6 {Black threatens to win material: Qd6xf4. Black forks: f4+d3} 17. Ne4 {
White threatens to win material: Ne4xd6} Qxf4 18. Kh1 (18. Rae1 e5 19. Qb3 Bc8
$14) 18... f5 (18... e5 $142 $5 $11 {would allow Black to play on}) 19. Nxc5
$16 Bc8 20. d4 Na6 (20... Rxd4 $142 21. Nd3 Qd6 22. Nxd4 Qxd4 $16) 21. Ne5 $4 {
throwing away the advantage} (21. Nxa6 Bxa6 22. Qa4 Bb7 23. Qxa7 Qc7 $16) 21...
Qg5 $4 {not a good decision, because now the opponent is right back in the game
} (21... Qxd4 22. Ncd3 $17) 22. Nxc6 $4 {weakening the position} (22. Nxa6 $5
Bxa6 23. Qa4 $16) 22... Rd6 $4 {Black threatens to win material: Rd6xc6. with
this move Black loses his initiative} (22... Nxc5 23. Nxd8 Rxd8 $17) 23. Nxa7
$4 {a transit from better to worse} (23. Ne4 $142 fxe4 24. Rxf8+ Kxf8 25. Rf1+
Ke8 26. Ne5 Rxd4 27. Qa4+ Bd7 28. Nxd7 Rxd7 29. Qxa6 $16) 23... Nxc5 $17 24.
Nb5 Rdd8 25. Rf3 (25. a4 Bb7 26. Ra3 Rf6 $19) 25... Bb7 26. Rg3 Qh6 $4 {
releasing the pressure on the opponent} (26... Qh5 $142 {and the scales tip in
favour of Black} 27. Kg1 Ne4 $19) 27. dxc5 $11 Rd2 (27... f4 $142 $5 {must
definitely be considered} 28. Rf3 Qh5 $11) 28. Qc3 $16 g6 29. Nd6 Rd8 $4 {
further deteriorates the position} (29... Bc6 30. Qc1 Qf4 $11) 30. Qf6 $18 Rf8
(30... Qf8 {desperation} 31. Qxe6+ Kh8 $18) 31. Qxe6+ Kg7 (31... Kh8 32. Nf7+
Rxf7 33. Qxf7 Rxb2 34. Rd1 Bxg2+ 35. Rxg2 Rb8 36. Qf6+ Qg7 37. Rd8+ Rxd8 38.
Qxd8+ Qg8 39. Qxg8+ Kxg8 40. c6 f4 41. c7 f3 42. c8=Q+ Kg7 43. Qc7+ Kf6 44. Rg3
f2 45. Rf3+ Ke6 46. Rxf2 h5 47. Rf7 h4 48. Qe7#) 32. Qe7+ Kg8 33. Qxb7 Qh5 (
33... g5 34. h4 $1 {doomsday} Re2 35. Rxg5+ Kh8 36. g3 $18) 34. Qf3 Qh6 (34...
Qxf3 {cannot change destiny} 35. gxf3 Rxb2 36. Rg2 Rxg2 37. Kxg2 $18) 35. Qe3 (
35. Nxf5 $142 {and White wins} Rxf5 36. Qxf5 $18) 35... Qxe3 36. Rxe3 f4 (36...
Rxb2 {is no salvation} 37. a4 $18) 37. Rb3 g5 (37... Ra8 {does not improve
anything} 38. Kg1 $18) 38. Rf1 g4 (38... Ra8 {is not much help} 39. a3 $18) 39.
Rb7 f3 (39... h5 {doesn't improve anything} 40. h3 $18) 40. g3 (40. gxf3 $142 {
and the rest is a matter of technique} Rd4 $18) 40... h5 (40... h6 {doesn't
change anything anymore} 41. a4 $18) 41. Ne4 (41. a4 $5 {seems even better} Ra8
42. Ne4 Re2 $18) 41... Rd4 42. Nf2 Rxc4 43. b4 Re8 (43... Rf7 {does not help
much} 44. Rb8+ Rf8 45. Rxf8+ Kxf8 46. Nd3 $18) 44. h3 gxh3 (44... Re6 {doesn't
get the cat off the tree} 45. a4 $18) 45. Nxh3 Rf8 (45... Ra8 {doesn't improve
anything} 46. Rf2 $18) 46. Nf4 Rc3 47. Nxh5 f2 (47... Rf7 {doesn't change the
outcome of the game} 48. Rb8+ Kh7 49. a4 $18) 48. Kg2 Rff3 49. Rxf2 (49. Rxf2
Rxf2+ 50. Kxf2 Rc2+ 51. Kf3 Rc3+ 52. Ke4 Kh8 53. a4 Kg8 54. a5 Ra3 55. c6 Rc3
56. c7 Kf8 57. a6 Rc4+ 58. Kf5 Rc3 59. a7 Rf3+ 60. Ke4 Re3+ 61. Kxe3 Kf7 62.
c8=Q+ Kg6 63. Qg8+ Kxh5 64. Rh7#) 1-0

